TASK 1:
       List all the main components you find inside a desktop PC after opening the cabinet, and write a short description (1-2 lines) for each.


==============================================================================================
|            Component	             |                   Short Description                   |
==============================================================================================
|Motherboard	                       |   The main circuit board that connects and allows     |                      
|                                    |   communication between all hardware components.      |
|------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
|CPU (Central Processing Unit)	     |   The computer's "brain" that performs calculations   |
|                                    |   and executes instructions.                          |
|------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
|CPU Cooler (Heatsink & Fan)	       |   Removes heat generated by the CPU to prevent        |
|                                    |   overheating.                                        |
|------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
|RAM (Random Access Memory)          |   Temporary high-speed memory used by programs and    |
|                                    |   the operating system while running.                 |
|------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
|Power Supply Unit (PSU)             |   Converts AC power from the wall outlet into DC      |
|                                    |   power for the computer components.                  |
|------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
|Storage Drive (SSD/HDD)	           |   Stores the operating system, software, and user     |
|                                    |   files. SSDs are faster; HDDs usually offer more     |
|                                    |   storage at lower cost.                              |
|------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
|Graphics Card (GPU)	               |   Processes graphics, video, and gaming workloads.    |
|                                    |   Some PCs use integrated graphics instead.           |
|------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
|Expansion Cards                     |   Optional cards (sound card, Wi-Fi card, capture     |
|                                    |   card, etc.) installed in motherboard slots to add   |
|                                    |   features.                                           |
|------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
|CMOS Battery	                       |   Small battery that powers the motherboard's clock   |
|                                    |   and BIOS settings when the PC is turned off.        |
|------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
|Cables and Connectors	             |   Power cables and data cables that connect           |
|                                    |   components such as drives, fans, and the            |
|                                    |   motherboard.                                        |
|------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
|M.2 SSD 	                           |   A compact storage device mounted directly on the    |
|                                    |   motherboard for high-speed data access.             |
|------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
|Front Panel Connectors              |   Wires connecting the case's power button, reset     |
|                                    |   button, USB ports, and audio jacks to the           |
|                                    |   motherboard.                                        |
==============================================================================================




